A '''Jack of all trades, master of none''' is a person who is competent with many skills but is not very good with one particular skill. The term has become a cliche.

The above is actually a shortened version of the true phrase. The phrase in its entirety is as follows; "Jack of all trades, master of none, though ofttimes better than master of one". This complete phrasing of the term would seem to remove any negative connotations which follow the labeling as such in the former form.

